  "prompt": "Is Australia considered part of the U.K?",
  "response": "No, Australia is not considered part of the United Kingdom. Australia is a sovereign nation and a member of the Commonwealth of Nations. It has its own constitution, government, and legal system. While Australia was formerly a colony of the British Empire and shares a historical connection with the U.K., it gained legislative independence with the Statute of Westminster in 1931 and further solidified its status as an independent nation with the passage of the Australia Act in 1986. Australia does, however, recognize the British monarch as its head of state, represented by the Governor-General.",
